A social commentator, Reno Omokri, has commended All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential aspirant, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, for his urgent visit to the scene of the Owo Church massacre in Ondo State. He, however, told Tinubu that the Owo Medical Centre have urgent need for finances and blood to attend to the victims that sustained injuries during the church attack by terrorists last Sunday, urging him to make donations.
Omokri in his official twitter handle Reno Omokri @renoomokri wrote: “I commend Bola Tinubu for speedily visiting the scene of the Owo killings, at St. Francis Catholic Church, Owo. This shows leadership.
“Right now, the Federal Medical Centre, Owo, needs finances and blood donations. I know that Asiwaju has the means, and I encourage him to donate!”
